>Jason Coan wrote:
>
> > From: "Jason Coan" <COANJ@...>
> >
> > well, at 14th level you have a couple choices, money, or power level up
>to about 20 when you can go kill monsters that have real money. Personally
>I chose to power level from 12 to 20 killing gators in oasis, didn't make a
>dime, actually lost money due to having to buy food and water. But once I
>hit 20, I went to some better places where the money is great. Now I'm
>28th lvl and have more money than I know what to do with. In fact I just
>bought a 250pp bow, spent 100pp for a SBH for a buddy of mine, spent
>antother 100pp equiping a buddy who lost his body and GMs refused to help,
>and I'm still sitting on enough for a couple pieces of real plate, and
>looking to spend another 400-500pp on a couple tommys. My point is, at
>14th lvl, I know of nowhere to go make GREAT money, so if you can just bear
>to be poor for another 6 levels (which go fast killing gators), you'll be
>strong enough to go fight stuff that dropps several plat at a time....at
>which point you'll be quickly equip yourself then wonder "where to I spend
>all this money?" :)
